feedback: if dist_type="Normal" then "The values are distributed reasonably symmetrically." elseif dist_type="Normal with Outlier" then "The values are reasonably symmetric, but there is one value that is much larger than the rest, and possibly a mistake in recording." elseif dist_type="Bimodal" then "There seems to be two clusters of values, possibly from two different types of apples." elseif dist_type="Left Skew" then "The distribution is skew with mainly high values and a long tail to the left." elseif dist_type="Right Skew" then "The distribution is skew with mainly low values and a long tail to the right."

